\title{Standard Integrals \#3}

Important integrals like 
\small\[ \int \tan x \cdot dx, \int \frac{dx}{x^2-a^2}, \int \frac{dx}{\sqrt{x^2+a^2}}
\]\normalsize

reason.tex:
%text The following integrals are rather important and should be remembered The results are being presented without proof. However, with the correct substitution, one can derive all of the following results
% \begin{align} \begin{tabular}{MN}
\hline \text{Integral} & \text{Evaluates to} \\ \hline \int\tan x\cdot dx & \log \vert \sec x \vert + C \\ \hline \int \cot x \cdot dx & \log\vert \sin x \vert + C \\ \hline \int \sec x\cdot dx & \log\vert \sec x + \tan x\vert + C \\ \hline \int \csc x \cdot dx & \log\vert \csc x - \cot x\vert + C \\ \hline \int \frac{dx}{x^2-a^2} & \frac{1}{2a}\cdot \log \left\vert \frac{x-a}{x+a}\right\vert + C \\ \hline \int \frac{dx}{a^2-x^2} & \frac{1}{2a}\cdot \log \left\vert \frac{a-x}{a+x}\right\vert + C \\ \hline \int \frac{dx}{x^2 + a^2} & \frac{1}{a}\cdot\tan^{-1} \left(\frac{x}{a} \right) + C \\ \hline \int \frac{dx}{\sqrt{x^2-a^2}} & \log \vert x + \sqrt{x^2-a^2} \vert + C \\ \hline \int \frac{dx}{\sqrt{x^2+a^2}} & \log \vert x + \sqrt{x^2+a^2} \vert + C \\ \hline \int \frac{dx}{\sqrt{a^2-x^2}} & \sin^{-1} \left(\frac{x}{a} \right) + C \\ \hline \end{tabular} \end{align} %text %
